  <p class=3DMsoNormal>Weapon Preference: Missiles<o:p></o:p></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>The Tarapin are a medium sized Amphibian with a mix =
of
  blue and orange skin.<o:p></o:p></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span class=3DSpellE>Tarapins</span> used to only ex=
ist as
  slaves to the <span class=3DSpellE>Keskudon</span> race, long ago conquer=
ed by
  them. At the same point in history that the <span class=3DSpellE>Keskudon=
s</span>
  were inexplicably reduced to a very small part of the Galaxy, the <span
  class=3DSpellE>Tarapins</span> broke free from their bondage.<o:p></o:p><=
/p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span class=3DSpellE>Tarapins</span> do not age for
  exceptionally long periods of time, so long that it is rare for a Tarapin=
 to
  die of old age. It is a very big event amongst <span class=3DSpellE>Tarap=
ins</span>
  when one does. Because of this longevity, many Tarapin are surviving form=
er
  slaves, still holding the marks of their slavery on their skin.<o:p></o:p=
></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span class=3DSpellE>Tarapins</span> live as familia=
l clans.
  Each family holding their name of great importance. The greatest insult a
  Tarapin uses against another Tarapin translates to something equal to
  &quot;May your name die&quot;. The clans do not often conflict and many <=
span
  class=3DGramE>long lasting</span> clan alliances are honored for
  generations--though the primary focus for any Tarapin is the betterment of
  their own name.</p>
